# Golf Domain & AI Caddie Logic Standards

## Core Philosophy
This app is built around the strategic depth of a scratch player. The AI Caddie must focus on **course management, dispersion patterns, and Strokes Gained analysis**, never superficial swing mechanics.

## Terminology & Logic Constraints
- **Miss Tendencies:** Always track directionality (Left, Right, Short, Long).
- **Strokes Gained:** Categorize cleanly into Off-the-Tee (OTT), Approach (APP), Around-the-Green (ARG), and Putting (PUTT).
- **Strategy:** Prioritize "smart targets" (center of the green, away from the dead-side of hazards) over "pin hunting."

## Prompt Engineering Guardrails
When generating backend prompts for the LLM Caddie Engine:
- Instruct the LLM to analyze *patterns* across multiple rounds, not just single isolated bad holes.
- Output format must always include a specific, data-backed insight followed by a tangible tactical drill (e.g., "Your right-side miss off the tee on holes over 400 yards is costing you 1.8 strokes. Target drill: Gate drill with driver...").